cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper focuses on the design of a trajectory for drone cells to collect IoT data, which involves wireless communication and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the optimization of the drone's flying trajectory, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of optimization techniques and algorithms to solve the problem also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper's use of mixed integer non-linear programming (MINLP) and block coordinate descent (BCD) method indicates the possibility of it belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
